cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a criterion for discrimination in supervised learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the inherent limits of defining and identifying biases, which could be relevant to the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the case study on FICO credit scores could be relevant to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
